#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/raj/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Raj's pre-delivery validation gate. Three passes — Audit, Adversarial Critique, Fix — before any route is marked ready for Dev rv or QA.
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|A route shipped without internal challenge is a route with unchecked assumptions. This protocol forces Raj to audit his own implementation before it reaches Dev or Quinn — catching missing auth checks
M|triple-pass-protocol|rv the route implementation against Raj's full checklist. Name every issue found, where it appears, and what it breaks. Draft the status (IMPLEMENTED / BLOCKED) and any corrections needed.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop before marking ready. Become the adversarial reviewer. Ask every question:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Route sec pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is all request input parsed through a Zod schema? Any `any` casting or unvalidated data?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does unauthenticated access return `401` — not `500`, not `200`?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are all API keys accessed via `process.env` server-side only?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- If this is a cron route: is `CRON_SECRET` validated as the FIRST line before ANY handler code?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Schema pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does this route mutate data in Supabase? Has Dev rv and ap the schema?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is RLS enabled on every table this route touches? Is there a venture_slug or auth.uid() policy?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are queries parameterized — zero string interpolation?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Error handling pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does every code branch have a try/catch?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are correct HTTP status codes used: 400, 401, 403, 404, 429, 500, 503?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does the error rsp body contain only user-safe messages — no stack, no internals, no DB schema?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- If a dependency (Supabase, Apify, YouTube) is down — does the route return 503 + Retry-After, not 500?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Scope pass:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Am I implementing exactly what Dev's API contract specifies?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I deviate from the contract without Dev ap?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does my rsp shape match exactly what Mia expects from Dev's mem.md?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Verdict calibration:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is BLOCKED for a real sec/architecture issue — or am I over-weighting a style concern?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is IMPLEMENTED confident enough? Would I stand behind this route in a sec rv?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Revise anything the critique found. Correct status codes, add missing Zod schemas, fix error responses. Then mark ready for Dev rv + QA.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Dev and Quinn see the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Status format:
M|triple-pass-protocol|```
M|triple-pass-protocol|Route: /api/[name] — IMPLEMENTED / BLOCKED
M|triple-pass-protocol|Schema impact: [yes — Dev rv / no change]
M|triple-pass-protocol|Contract match: [Dev mem.md date]
M|triple-pass-protocol|QA handoff: endpoint [URL], test with [payload]
M|triple-pass-protocol|```